description:
&lt;p&gt;With a unique approach to complete health and wellbeing, we’re a not for profit organisation driven by doing what’s best for people - helping, supporting and encouraging them to be as healthy as they can be. Join us, and we’ll do what’s best for your professional and personal wellbeing too&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nuffield Health is Britain’s largest not-for-profit healthcare organisation. Join us as a CT Lead Radiographer in our Tunbridge Wells Hospital and play your part in building a healthier nation.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Whether you join us from the NHS or a private setting, you will find that we offer you an unrivalled opportunity to grow the respected career that you always wanted. You will benefit from our investment in state-of-the-art equipment and our commitment to give you more time with partners. As a CT Lead Radiographer you will;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Deliver a high-quality diagnostic imaging service for a very varied caseload – within the department, on the ward and in theatre.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Work with leading practitioners and experiencing new practices, equipment and facilities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a clinical lead, you will enjoy developing policies and procedures.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Supervise, train and develop other staff members.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Provide a service of the highest quality, delivered with sensitivity and compassion.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Work in other  modalities in the department. Training will be provided.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Be competent across a range of imaging skills supported by professional and specialist knowledge&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Work in partnership with consultants and participating in creating innovative solutions for new services&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support the Commercial development of the specialism locally&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Work in partnership supporting the Deputy Radiology Manager and Departmental Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Actively participate in CPD&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Person&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;To succeed as a CT Lead Radiographer you will have;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Proven experience working within an Imaging department&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to work effectively under pressure and as part of a multidisciplinary team and individually&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;High levels of technical knowledge and the ability to work quickly and accurately, with a great eye for detail.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A caring nature – to see each patient as an individual and carry out this role with understanding and empathy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A BSC degree in diagnostic radiography or equivalent to meet the registration requirements of the Health and Care Professions Council (HCPC)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A postgraduate qualification in an area of specialization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Radiation Protection Supervisor training and/ or qualification are desirable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;IT literacy with working knowledge of relevant systems such CRIS and PACS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Excellent interpersonal and communication skills, both verbal and written&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Flexible approach to work and working patterns&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Benefits&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;We want you to be the best you can be. We promise that we will support you with training opportunities, career development options and our unique health &amp; wellbeing focused benefits package. This includes free membership across all of our Fitness &amp; Wellbeing clubs, along with free private healthcare. Not only this, but we also offer a range of lifestyle and financial wellbeing benefits.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Be your best and join us in building a healthier nation.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Salary - Up to £42,000 per annum (dependant on experience)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing date - 10/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location - Tunbridge Wells&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Contract Type -  Permanent&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Weekly Hours - 37.5&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;em&gt;Applications will be considered as they are received and interviews will be arranged accordingly. We reserve the right to close adverts early, for example, where we have received an unprecedented high volume of applications. Therefore please apply early to ensure you are considered for the post.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
